reviewText: DVD would not play!  Total RIPOFF!!
it was an import and, of course, did not work on my dvd player.
I was sold a DVD formatted for DVD regions 2,4 and 5 which will not work on DVD players in the US. Felt very disappointed ripped off!

A precursor to Casablanca - Warner Bros. is trying to alert the American neutrality folks about the threat of fascism before we got attacked at Pearl Harbor. This film features grand typecasting, film noir lighting, corny wisecracks and a number of doors being broken down.  It really cannot decide if it wants to be a comedy or a mystery or a spy thriller.  But with elements of each, it is very entertaining.
